The article discusses the importance of passing tax reform in the US and highlights the benefits of the proposed Tax Cuts and Jobs Act. Both the House and Senate have plans for tax reform that include tax cuts for all income levels and simplification of the tax code. The plans also aim to make businesses more competitive and create jobs. The Joint Committee on Taxation has confirmed that both versions of the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act would reduce taxes for everyone, with middle income households seeing the greatest benefits. The article also mentions that a study by the Council of Economic Advisors suggests that a 20 percent corporate rate could lead to increased household wages. Overall, passing tax reform is seen as a way for the GOP to demonstrate its commitment to the American people and stimulate economic growth.